{
  "texts": [
    "This distinction presents a crucial paragon for understanding the limitations of AI systems. 2.",
    "Limitations of AI: We argue that current AI technologies cannot achieve advanced general intelligence (AGI) due to their reliance on human input for data and their inability to possess agency, world modeling and moral understanding.",
    "Therefore, they are not able to reach or surpass human intelligence. 3.",
    "Ethical implications:The exponential progress of AI raises significant ethical concerns, including issues of data privacy, intellectual property, and the potential displacement of human jobs.",
    "We hereby advocate for the establishment of a comprehensive framework for AI ethics to address the current and future challenges. 4."
  ]
}